==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pterotic
<hw>Pte*ro"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ wing +
<?/, <?/, ear.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to, or
designating, a bone between the prootic and epiotic in the dorsal and
outer part of the periotic capsule of many fishes.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The pterotic bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>pterotic bone</xex> is so called because
fancied in some cases to resemble in form a bird's wing</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pterygium</ent>⟦br⟧
